The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Twelfth seed Mudit Kedia and 15th seed Rohan Sagar Ahuja were shown the doors in the first round of the boys under-12 category of the Bumchums Calcutta Hardcourt Tennis Championships at the South Club on Saturday. Kedia was beaten by Raghav Ruia 7-8 (8-10) while Rohan Priy Karnani defeated Ahuja 8-6.

 To commemorate the first birth anniversary of the Dibyendu Barua Chess Academy (DBCA), Arjuna awardee Grandmaster Surya Sekhar Ganguly will be felicitated jointly by DBCA and Lions Club of Calcutta on Monday. 

 Surya Sekhar will later play a simultaneous match against 25 trainees of the Academy. City police commissioner Prasun Mukherjee will be the Chief Guest. Chuni Goswami and Sailen will also be present.

 Bengal Amateur Boxing Federation (BABF) will organise a camp for the men and women pugilists of the state at the newly constructed Rony Moore ring at the Body Guard Lines. The camp will commence on Tuesday and will run till September 20. Mohammed Ali Qamar will be the chief coach for the camp. 

 BASKETBALL: Sub-junior National finals at the Netaji Indoor Stadium from 3 pm.




